                "text": "yeah I am hoping the reactive runtime gives it an uber-tight feedback loop. The feedback is the environment, not the training data. I often see the agent initially cannot call its own tools properly at first, but after round 10 it is warmed up and very productive. The early failures are because I have not optimized the prompt yet, its often completely out-of-whack with what I have actually implemented, but also, I don't really need to, coz the environment is the strong feedback signal.\n\nYes its also pretty bad at overall architecture, but it is "
              },
