              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " at copying established patterns. Robocoop3 itself is so much better than my previous LLM project, written in a tenth of the time coz I figured out how to get it it to port the agent loop from OpenCode.\n\nMost of my prompts are: Look at X, Y Z, now do it in C. Usually X, Y and Z is something I wrote a few years ago. OpenCode port was the first time I ported 3rd party code, its MIT licensed and I attribute it. I think that unblocks a ton of options of remixing. So unless every aspect of a project is totally rethought from the ground up, I think you can actually very easily make a game if you have a game that has somewhat the right architecture in place.\n\nits gonna insane in another year's time"
